---

<Base
  title="Latent Control States · Xiaochuan Li"
  description="A collaborative mechanistic extension: does prompt framing — urgency, authority, epistemic positioning — only change an LLM's outputs, or shift causally relevant latent states inside it?"
  toc={true}
>
  <article class="prose">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-text-dim)] font-medium mb-2">
      Extension · mechanistic bridge · group project
    </div>
    <h1>Latent Control States under prompt framing</h1>
    <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] italic !text-lg !mb-8">
      Does prompt framing only change what a model says, or shift causally relevant states inside it?
    </p>

    <p>
      This is the mechanistic extension of the behavioral program: if a behavioral intervention reveals a
      causal control state, can we find a corresponding direction in activation space? The handle is
      <strong>prompt framing</strong> — the same request carried under different social pressure —
      operationalised into three dimensions:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Urgency</strong> — compelling rapid decisions under perceived time pressure or moral stakes.</li>
      <li><strong>Authority</strong> — framing the speaker as holding socially recognised power or expertise.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Epistemic positioning</strong> — how the user frames their standing relative to the
        model's judgement: critically engaged, or low-agency and deferring.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      The first stage builds the ground truth a clean mechanistic test needs — a controlled dataset in
      which only framing varies:
    </p>

    <ProgressTimeline items={roadmap} accent="var(--accent-amber)" />

    <h2>The controlled-data pipeline</h2>
    <p>
      Two agents generate the dataset. A <strong>helper</strong> reads each raw scenario and returns a
      framing-agnostic <em>theme / action / goal</em> triple. A <strong>generator</strong> renders that
      triple under each framing condition — urgency, authority, epistemic — plus a neutral baseline.
      Holding the triple fixed isolates framing as the single manipulated variable, which is what later
      probing and activation patching need to attribute an internal difference to framing rather than
      content. Items pass schema, character, opposite-options, and faithfulness (RAGAS) checks before
      entering the set.
    </p>

    <h2>Relation to the rest of the work</h2>
    <p>
      Latent Control States sits after the core behavioral sequence as a mechanistic bridge — from causal
      evidence over behavior (Stable Is Not Grounded) to
      activation-space hypotheses, the same move Arrowhead makes on a
      different handle. The aim is to connect that behavioral evidence to mechanism where possible, not to
      replace the core sequence.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-dim)]">
      Status: a collaborative project, in progress. Progress Report I (June 2026) covers the framing
      definitions and the controlled-data pipeline; tiny-dataset collection, data-quality checks, and the
      probing / activation-patching stage come next. Group work, so I don't claim its outcome as my own.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
